.B XTR_LOG(SINK, \&...) 
Basic log macro, logs the specified format string and arguments to the given sink, blocking if the sink is full. The non\-blocking variant of this macro is XTR_TRY_LOG which will discard the message if the sink is full. Timestamps are read in the background thread\-\-\-if this is undesirable use XTR_LOG_RTC or XTR_LOG_TSC which read timestamps at the point of logging. 
