.B class  xtr::logger 
The main logger class. When constructed a background thread will be created which is used for formatting log messages and performing I/O. To write to the logger call \fI\%xtr::logger::get_sink\fP to create a sink, then pass the sink to a macro such as XTR_LOG (see the \fI\%creating and writing to sinks\fP section of the user guide for details). 
